Drop sprite PNGs here to replace the placeholder art. File name = the entity /
tile key; assets.py picks them up automatically, and any missing file falls back
to the code-drawn shape. Run `python make_assets.py` to (re)generate this whole
starter set.

UNITS & BUILDINGS (any size; drawn centred on the tile):
  worker.png
  transporter_s.png  miner_s.png  dozer_s.png
  truck_m.png  excavator_m.png  dozer_m.png  mega.png
  workshop.png  oven.png  crusher.png  arc_furnace.png

TILES (must keep the pointy-top hex proportions or they won't line up):
  tile_andesite.png  tile_diorite.png  tile_granite.png
  tile_basalt.png    tile_rhyolite.png                 <- solid rock (iso cubes)
  tile_rubble.png    tile_excavated.png  tile_road.png <- dug floor

  Canvas ratio must be  W : H  =  sqrt(3) : 2  (e.g. 111 x 128).
  The hexagon must fill the whole canvas edge-to-edge, pointy side up:
      - top vertex   at (W/2, 0)
      - bottom vertex at (W/2, H)
      - left / right vertices at x=0 and x=W, y=H/2
  Rock tiles read as a raised cube (light top face + two darker side faces);
  the two VERTICAL edges (left & right) are the blocked E/W sides. Floor tiles
  are a flat, darker recessed hex. The starter PNGs are exact templates — open
  them to trace the shape.
